# Language Usage Guidelines

## Commit Messages
- **ALWAYS use English** for commit messages
- Follow conventional commit format: `type(scope): description`
- Examples:
  - `feat: add React-Flow integration system`
  - `fix: resolve build errors in layout-engine`
  - `docs: update API documentation`
  - `refactor: improve type safety in validators`

## Code and Comments
- **ALWAYS use English** for:
  - Variable names, function names, class names
  - Code comments and documentation
  - Log messages and error messages
  - Interface definitions and type annotations
  - Test descriptions and assertions

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: English code and comments
interface WorkflowValidator {
  // Validates workflow data structure
  validate(data: WorkflowData): ValidationResult;
}

// ❌ WRONG: Korean in code
interface 워크플로우검증기 {
  // 워크플로우 데이터 구조를 검증합니다
  검증(데이터: WorkflowData): ValidationResult;
}
```

## Documentation
### English Documentation (Default)
- **ALWAYS use English** for:
  - README.md files
  - API documentation  
  - Technical specifications
  - Architecture documents
  - Code examples and tutorials

### Korean Documentation (Exception)
- **ONLY use Korean** for files in `.design/` folder:
  - `.design/robota-saas-website/*.md`
  - Project planning documents
  - Internal design specifications
  - Business requirement documents

### File Examples
```
✅ ENGLISH:
- README.md
- docs/api-reference/
- packages/*/README.md
- CONTRIBUTING.md

✅ KOREAN: 
- .design/robota-saas-website/FEATURES.md
- .design/robota-saas-website/ARCHITECTURE.md
- .design/robota-saas-website/REACT-FLOW-INTEGRATION-TASKS.md
```

## Chat and Communication
- **Use Korean** for user communication and chat responses
- **Use English** for all code, technical terms, and implementation details within responses
- When showing code examples or technical solutions, use English even in Korean responses

## Enforcement
This rule applies to all development work and should be consistently followed across the entire codebase to maintain international collaboration standards while preserving Korean documentation for internal design processes.